    "description_long": "This object is a circular traffic sign mounted on a vertical post. The sign face is bordered with a bold red ring and has a light gray center, which is typical for regulatory or warning signs. The rear of the sign is a solid dark gray, likely metal, with visible mounting hardware at the top and bottom where it attaches to the post. The post itself is cylindrical, dark, and appears to be made of metal, providing sturdy support. The sign is designed to be highly visible to oncoming traffic, with the red border serving as a visual alert. There are no visible symbols or text on the sign face, suggesting it may be a placeholder or a generic sign.",
